{"TopicId":159660,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"I am running an ancient version of KSP","CreatedByName":"Ncog Nito","CreatedById":176269,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T14:50:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ncog Nito","CreatedById":176269,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T14:50:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello, does KSP search for updates when it is opened on your desktop? If so does it automatically download updates?\u00A0 If not where an I find the updates...I\u0027m running version 1.0.4.861...Help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T14:58:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223031699\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492959009\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176269\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ncog Nito\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Ncog Nito said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello, does KSP search for updates when it is opened on your desktop?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should give you some indication in the launcher... but that only started happening very recently. You won\u0027t have it in 1.0, as that still has the old patcher / updater and it\u0027s broken now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223031699\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492959009\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176269\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ncog Nito\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Ncog Nito said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf so does it automatically download updates?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP \u003Cem\u003Ehad\u003C/em\u003E a real updater, but it seems nobody can be bothered maintaining it... so the answer, as of the current version, is no.*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223031699\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492959009\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176269\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ncog Nito\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Ncog Nito said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf not where an I find the updates\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the same place you initially found KSP - the store if you bought direct, GOG if you bought from them.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI doubt there will be a 1.0 -\u0026gt; 1.2.2 patch, so you will probably have to download the whole thing and reinstall.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you\u0027re on MacOS or GNU/Linux there are no patches at all.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003E*I still think this situation is incredibly lame, and in case it\u0027s not obvious, I\u0027m not happy with it at all. Particularly as there are patches for Winblows only.\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003ELazy\u003C/span\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-23T15:02:08Z\u0022 title=\u002204/23/2017 03:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 23, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ncog Nito","CreatedById":176269,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T15:02:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait...Are you saying you have to buy the updates?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Harry Rhodan","CreatedById":119953,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T15:04:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223031712\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492959762\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176269\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ncog Nito\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Ncog Nito said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait...Are you saying you have to buy the updates?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, you go to the store you bought it in and download the newest version. If you bought it on Steam you have to start the Steam client to update your stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-23T15:04:37Z\u0022 title=\u002204/23/2017 03:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 23, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Harry Rhodan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T15:05:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223031712\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492959762\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176269\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ncog Nito\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Ncog Nito said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait...Are you saying you have to buy the updates?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCertainly not\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MiffedStarfish","CreatedById":175356,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T17:31:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can transfer saves and crafts by copying everything from your old save folder into the new save folder.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T21:37:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223031889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492968695\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175356\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MiffedStarfish\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, MiffedStarfish said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can transfer saves and crafts by copying everything from your old save folder into the new save folder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSave a copy of those files somewhere else though: not everything might transfer intact.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"technicalfool","CreatedById":70430,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-24T15:18:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition to what everyone else has said, depending on how well the game imports a 1.0.4 save file, you may want to keep the old version of KSP around for playing the old saves with. Just copy the whole thing to somewhere else before updating and you can have the two installations side by side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}